\tan \frac x2+\cot \frac x2
\tan \frac x2+\cot \frac x2=\frac 2{\sin x}
\sin x=2\sin \frac x2 \cos \frac x2
\sin^2 \frac x2+\cos^2 \frac x2=1
\tan \frac x2+\cot\frac x2=\frac{\sin \frac x2}{\cos \frac x2}+\frac{\cos \frac x2}{\sin \frac x2}=\frac{\sin^2 \frac x2+\cos^2\frac x2}{\cos \frac x2 \sin \frac x2}=\frac 2{\sin x}
